In the following I added the top5 results of the common giant panda example with inceptionv3 and inceptionv4 (with inceptionv4 the differences are fewer).

With Python 2 and inceptionv3 I get (panda example, top5):

Class 388 with prob: 0.840522
Class 384 with prob: 0.008873
Class 812 with prob: 0.005004
Class 387 with prob: 0.003787
Class 995 with prob: 0.001669

With Python 3 and inceptionv3 I get (panda example, top5):

Class 388 with prob: 0.816696
Class 384 with prob: 0.010089
Class 812 with prob: 0.004649
Class 387 with prob: 0.002653
Class 995 with prob: 0.001971

With Python 2 and inceptionv4 I get (panda example, top5):

Class 388 with prob: 0.891811
Class 387 with prob: 0.004732
Class 384 with prob: 0.002913
Class 378 with prob: 0.000739
Class 375 with prob: 0.000680

With Python 3 and inceptionv4 I get (panda example, top5):

Class 388 with prob: 0.897901

Class 384 with prob: 0.002632
Class 375 with prob: 0.000646
Class 378 with prob: 0.000644
